{"word":"H8581 - תַּעָב - taʻâb - taw-ab' - Abhor","slug":"H8581","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">תַּעָב</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>taʻâb"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>taw-ab'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Abhor"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05EA;&#x05BC;&#x05E2;&#x05D1; - ta&#x0302;&#x201B;ab</b> - <i>taw-ab'</i><p/>A primitive root; to <i>loathe</i>, that is, (morally) <i>detest: - </i>(make to be) abhor (-red), (be, commit more, do) abominable (-y), X utterly."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H8374\">H8374</a>, <a href=\"#/H8441\">H8441</a>"}]}